<title type="html"><![CDATA[1/27(Sat.) Does accent matter?/Popular kids(Host: Ken)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=118&amp;p=122#p122"><![CDATA[
Topic 1: Does accent matter?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dPcGhkRgnmU">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dPcGhkRgnmU</a><!-- m --><br />Q1.Does accent matter? In your opinion, which English accent sound the best? Are you copying American, British or Austrian accent?<br />Q2. Do you pursue perfect accent? Do you speak with strong accent? <br />Q3. Are you proud of or ashamed of your accent?  Have you struggled to understand some people's English? For example, Indian, Japanese and Filipino usually have strong accents in English?<br />Q4. Which is more important, accuracy (use the right grammar) or fluency（speak quickly without many pauses）?<br />Q5. What are the tips to sound more native?<br /><br />Topic 2: Popular kids<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rTvZtLAOa8k">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rTvZtLAOa8k</a><!-- m --><br />Q1. While in school, were you a popular kid? Did your try to act cool?<br />Q2.Do you agree with the study conclusion that popular kids usually end up to be terrible adults?<br />Q3. Have you had a crush on hot girls or bad boys while in school? Where are they now? As an adult, if you see them now, will you still find them attractive?<br />Q4. Have your done anything stupid because of peer pressure?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=89">AndrewWang</a> — Fri Jan 26, 2018 7:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
